               </state>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl1495-1">Assemani, ASMO, 54-59; BHO, 1149 ; Lagrange 61-64 ; Leclercq, III, 165-68. AMS, II, 254-60. Suhada ', I, 256-60. Delehaye, Actes, 439- 44, 558- 59. Wiessner, Miirtyrer, 144- 48. Trad. anglaise dans Brock-Harvey, Holy Women, 73-76.</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">After the execution of Simeon Bar Sabbaʿe, the wife of Shapur became sick. People accused the sister of Simeon, Tarbo, of witchcraft that caused the queen's sickness. Tarbo and her servant were arrested. They were tortured and cut into many pieces.</note>
